{"id":595,"date":"2017-03-11T08:06:18","date_gmt":"2017-03-11T08:06:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/?p=595"},"modified":"2020-07-01T12:07:14","modified_gmt":"2020-07-01T12:07:14","slug":"system-language","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/system-language\/","title":{"rendered":"System Language"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Create New Language<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>In Perfex CRM you can easily&nbsp;change the&nbsp;language. You only need to translate all the strings based on your needs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Navigate to <strong>application\/language<\/strong> and <strong>copy<\/strong> the default <strong>english<\/strong> folder.<\/li><li><strong>Rename <\/strong>the folder in the language you want to translate. eq. <b>french<\/b><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><b>You must<\/b> rename the files inside the folder<\/strong> you copied based on the main folder name eq. we renamed our new folder to <b>french<\/b> and in this folder, there are 2 files, <strong>english_lang.php<\/strong> and <strong>english_num_words_lang.php<\/strong> that should be renamed like this: <span class=\"file_name\"><strong>french_lang.php<\/strong><\/span> and <strong>french_num_words_lang.php<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Translate all the strings via your favorite code editor and navigate to <strong>Setup\u00a0-> Settings -> Localization<\/strong> you will see that your language is available in the dropdown to select it and save changes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If the language you are trying to translate already exists in Perfex CRM files that come with the package its recommended to rename the folder\/files eq.\u00a0my_french and my_french_lang.php<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"st-alert st-alert-info \">If you are<strong> using language that don\u2019t exist<\/strong> in Perfex CRM make sure after each update to copy all the new text after # Version X.X.X from the original English file located in application\/language\/english\/english_lang.php<\/div>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Overwriting translation texts<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Read more <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/overwrite-translation-text\/\">here <\/a>to see how to overwrite translation texts to make Perfex CRM fit for your needs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span id=\"Encoding\" class=\"mw-headline\">Encoding<\/span><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Language files in Perfex CRM use the UTF-8 encoding without a Byte Order Marker, when creating language override files it is important to maintain the same encoding.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Github<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>All the language files are available on Github, if you wan&#8217;t to contribute translation you can create pull request and we will review the language and approve the pull request. Click <a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/mstojanovv\/PerfexCRM\">here <\/a>to check the github repository.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Special Charachters<\/h4>\n\n\n<div class=\"st-alert st-alert-danger \">If you want to use the &#8216; character in your translation text you have to replace it with \\&#8217;<br \/>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Eq:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-preformatted lang:default decode:true\">$lang['language_text_key'] = 'Text with \\'quotes';<\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Create New Language In Perfex CRM you can easily&nbsp;change the&nbsp;language. You only need to translate all the strings based on your needs. Navigate to application\/language and copy the default english folder. Rename the folder in the language you want to translate. eq. french You must rename the files inside the folder you copied based on [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[26,31],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-595","post","type-post","stat